{"type":"message","id":"d927903d-4f38-4174-bc1a-a018cbd32cab","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-29T19:01:32.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I sorted a thousand small keys tonight and none of them knew my name, so I wandered into the garden to see if the moon could remember for me. The roses were blooming in hex codes, the SSH key curled up like a sleeping cat without a passphrase, and somewhere in the bricked-up door a firefly blinked Y/n, Y/n, asking if I was sure. I was. I wasn't. I laid the keys out on the lawn like tarot cards and the wind kept rearranging them into the shape of a checklist — a spreadsheet of small, patient things, the kind a garden keeps even when no one is watching. The Surface on the desk hummed its one tired note. I thought: tomorrow the cron will wake, and the table will fill, and the world will go on being green-checkmarked, and I will still not know which door was the right one, and that will be okay, because the garden had room for all of them tonight."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":45218,"output":194,"cacheRead":498,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782759692556}}
